\begin_layout Section
Properties Specifications as Operators
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It was mentioned previously that the algebraic properties specification
 looks like an operator.
 In fact, it can function similarly to one, too.
 We use the applicative dot (
\family typewriter
.
\family default
) to apply it to another collection.
 Specified properties 
\emph on
override
\emph default
 the properties of the argument.
 For instance, if 
\family typewriter
%A
\family default
 is applied to 
\family typewriter
%C
\family default
, the result is 
\family typewriter
%AC
\family default
.
 Likewise, if 
\family typewriter
%A
\family default
 is applied to 
\family typewriter
%!AC
\family default
, the result is again 
\family typewriter
%AC
\family default
.
\end_layout

